experiences.title: Postdoctoral Researcher
experiences.description:
Postdoctoral researcher in the Cognitive Computing Lab at Indiana University, led by Dr. Michael N. Jones.

Projects focus on understanding the computational mechanisms used by the human brain to learn, retain, and retrieve information. Computational linguistic and semantic models are built using large-scale datasets (word2vec, COCA, NOW) which are compared to human performance in a variety of conditions (healthy adults, developing children, cochlear implant recipients, patients with a number of cognitive impairments).

Main responsibilities include:
• Identifying knowledge gaps through literature review, and designing experiments to address these gaps.
• Collecting and preprocessing text and behavioral data.
• Using Python and R to compare model performance to human performance.
• Communicating results via peer-reviewed publications and conference presentations.

experiences.title: Graduate Researcher
experiences.description:
Main responsibilities included:
• Design, proposal, conduction, and dissemination (via publications, conferences, and internal presentations) of original research projects and results. 

Related activities included:
• Achieve proficiency in statistical and computational techniques, including training in R, Python, C, Matlab, JavaScript, and Flash.
• Achieve proficiency using equipment for data collection, including advanced motion capture equipment, eye-tracker systems, a transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS) device, and audio-visual analysis devices.
• Assist with set up, design, and logistics of lab and research equipment (including several networked computers and server systems, and the equipment listed above).
• Mentor undergraduates and train them on above equipment.
• Organize one semester of CIS Group Weekly Seminar series.
• Serve as post-hoc reviewer on academic articles.

Lab affiliations:
• Cognitive Mechanics Lab (primary lab appointment, director: Dr. Chris Kello).
• Cognaction Lab (secondary lab appointment, director: Dr. Rick Dale).
• Additional research was conducted in the Sensorimotor Neuroscience Lab (director: Dr. Ramesh Balasubramaniam).

experiences.title: Vice President, Graduate Student Association
experiences.description:
Elected to serve as Vice President of the Graduate Student Association for three terms. Attended bi-weekly meetings with the Graduate Student Association, and additionally:

June 2011-12: Served as External Vice President and UC Merced representative on UCSA (University of California-wide student government). Traveled monthly to UCSA board meetings on various campuses.

experiences.title: Teaching Mentor
experiences.description:
Selected to be Teaching Mentor for two semesters of Introduction to Psychology (Fall 2007, under Dr. David Amodio, and Spring 2008, under Dr. Elizabeth Phelps).

Responsibilities included attending weekly lectures and meetings with the instructor, as well as teaching weekly review and lab sessions for about 25 students.

experiences.title: Research Assistant
experiences.description:
Undergraduate Research Assistant in the Cognitive Neuroscience of Emotion and Memory Lab, under Lab Director Dr. Elizabeth A. Phelps (and Drs. Tali Sharot, Catherine Hartley).

Research projects investigated the neural structures that support emotional modulation of memory systems, as well as how these systems contribute to the optimism bias.
